## Create Apps

```bash
python manage.py startapp users
python manage.py startapp jobs
python manage.py startapp reviews
python manage.py startapp applications
python manage.py startapp common

User (AbstractUser)
  ├── role: [worker, customer, admin]
  ├── phone: CharField (unique)
  ├── district: FK → District
  └── is_verified: BooleanField

WorkerProfile
  ├── user: OneToOne → User
  ├── skills: M2M → TradeCategory
  ├── bio: TextField
  ├── hourly_rate: DecimalField
  ├── experience_years: IntegerField
  ├── rating: DecimalField (computed)
  └── portfolio_images: reverse FK

JobListing
  ├── customer: FK → User
  ├── category: FK → TradeCategory
  ├── title, description: CharField/TextField
  ├── district: FK → District
  ├── budget: DecimalField
  ├── urgency: [normal, urgent, asap]
  └── status: [open, in_progress, completed, cancelled]

JobApplication
  ├── job: FK → JobListing
  ├── worker: FK → User
  ├── cover_note: TextField
  ├── proposed_price: DecimalField
  └── status: [pending, accepted, rejected]

Review
  ├── job: FK → JobListing
  ├── reviewer: FK → User
  ├── reviewee: FK → User
  ├── rating: IntegerField (1–5)
  └── comment: TextField

Message
  ├── conversation: FK → Conversation
  ├── sender: FK → User
  ├── content: TextField
  └── timestamp: DateTimeField

TradeCategory
  └── name_uz, name_ru: CharField  (e.g. "Santexnik", "Электрик")

District
  └── name_uz, name_ru: CharField  (e.g. "Chilonzor", "Yunusobod")
